### Diagram sources

**A. Gemini prompt**

"The central node is addDocument, a function defined in apps/discovery-core/src/document/document.controller.ts (class DocumentController). It has no known programmatic callers — it is invoked by the NestJS HTTP router on POST /documents/:sourceId (entry point). addDocument calls: Logger.log, randomUUID, asyncHelper.executeAsync, documentService.addDocument, documentRepository.createDocument, markdownService.parse, pdfService.import, analysisService.addTextAnalysis, textService.createTextNodes, collectionService.associateDocument, terminologyService.getTerminologyFromCollection, enrichment.addDocument — each with an arrow pointing out from addDocument. Annotate the following as labeled side nodes connected with dashed edges: Neo4j DB write via documentRepository.createDocument — database, Neo4j DB write via textService.createTextNodes — database, Neo4j DB write/read via collectionService.associateDocument — database, Neo4j DB read via terminologyService.getTerminologyFromCollection — database, HTTP POST /enrichments/trigger via enrichment.addDocument — network, HTTP GET /enrichments/transaction/:id via enrichment.addDocument — network. Draw this as a directed call graph, not a flowchart. Use a horizontal left-to-right layout: callers on the left, the central function in the middle, callees on the right. Use rectangular nodes for functions, cylinder nodes for databases, cloud nodes for network calls. Label all edges with the direction of the call."

---

